[22:30.60]CAIUS LUCIUS	'Lack, good youth!
[22:32.19]	Thou movest no less with thy complaining than
[22:35.95]	Thy master in bleeding: say his name, good friend.
[22:39.85]IMOGEN	Richard du Champ.
[22:41.52]	[Aside]
[22:42.38]	If I do lie and do
[22:44.19]	No harm by it, though the gods hear, I hope
[22:47.66]	They'll pardon it.--Say you, sir?
[22:50.26]CAIUS LUCIUS	Thy name?
[22:51.35]IMOGEN	Fidele, sir.
[22:52.58]CAIUS LUCIUS	Thou dost approve thyself the very same:
[22:55.90]	Thy name well fits thy faith, thy faith thy name.
[22:59.80]	Wilt take thy chance with me? I will not say
[23:03.42]	Thou shalt be so well master'd, but, be sure,
